{"type":"message","id":"8287c721","parentId":"a4febfb5","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:03:19.138Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"yt-dlp installation needs pip which isn't available. Let me update the skill documentation to note this and provide alternative instructions:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a13953071ebdfd03","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/skills/youtube-research/SKILL.md","oldText":"## Requirements\n\n- `YOUTUBE_KEY` in `.env` file (YouTube Data API v3 key)\n- Python 3.6+ (standard library only for basic usage)\n- `yt-dlp` for transcript extraction (recommended): `pip install yt-dlp`\n\n**Note:** Search and video details work without yt-dlp. Transcript extraction is more reliable with yt-dlp installed.","newText":"## Requirements\n\n- `YOUTUBE_KEY` in `.env` file (YouTube Data API v3 key)\n- Python 3.6+ (standard library only for basic usage)\n- `yt-dlp` for reliable transcript extraction: install via pip, apt, or download binary\n\n**Install yt-dlp:**\n```bash\n# Option 1: pip (recommended)\npip install yt-dlp\n\n# Option 2: apt (Linux)\nsudo apt install yt-dlp\n\n# Option 3: Download binary (any OS)\n# See: https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp#installation\n```\n\n**Note:** Search and video details work without yt-dlp. Transcript extraction requires yt-dlp."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":30518,"output":296,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30814,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774792972059,"responseId":"chatcmpl-813e0338359e4cb5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9531613","parentId":"8287c721","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:03:19.158Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a13953071ebdfd03","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/skills/youtube-research/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  26 ## Requirements\n  27 \n  28 - `YOUTUBE_KEY` in `.env` file (YouTube Data API v3 key)\n  29 - Python 3.6+ (standard library only for basic usage)\n- 30 - `yt-dlp` for transcript extraction (recommended): `pip install yt-dlp`\n+ 30 - `yt-dlp` for reliable transcript extraction: install via pip, apt, or download binary\n  31 \n- 32 **Note:** Search and video details work without yt-dlp. Transcript extraction is more reliable with yt-dlp installed.\n+ 32 **Install yt-dlp:**\n+ 33 ```bash\n+ 34 # Option 1: pip (recommended)\n+ 35 pip install yt-dlp\n  33 \n+ 37 # Option 2: apt (Linux)\n+ 38 sudo apt install yt-dlp\n+ 39 \n+ 40 # Option 3: Download binary (any OS)\n+ 41 # See: https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp#installation\n+ 42 ```\n+ 43 \n+ 44 **Note:** Search and video details work without yt-dlp. Transcript extraction requires yt-dlp.\n+ 45 \n  34 ## Core Workflows\n  35 \n  36 ### 1. Search Videos\n  37 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":30},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774792999155}}
