{"type":"message","id":"c0d49abc","parentId":"8c1a216d","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:27:51.040Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes, exactly! That's the one - **jdepoix/youtube-transcript-api**. It scrapes the YouTube page and extracts captions using the same method YouTube's player uses, but handles all the complexity (track selection, formatting, etc.). **What it does:** - Fetches auto-generated and manual captions - Returns transcript with timestamps - Handles multiple languages - Works without any API key **Want me to update the skill to use this package?** I'll need to: 1. Update the script to use `youtube-transcript-api` instead of the timedtext API 2. Add proper fallback handling 3. Update the documentation This would make transcript extraction much more reliable. Should I proceed?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":33205,"output":144,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33349,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774794457735,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b194a84c421e983f"}}
