{"type":"message","id":"8b7905ad","parentId":"d4a11da2","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:41:06.994Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The earlier success was a fluke - YouTube is now blocking the IP (this is a VM). The youtube-transcript-api doesn't work from cloud providers.\n\nLet me update the skill to handle this limitation and provide alternatives:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-85f21ab01d741261","name":"edit","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/youtube-research/SKILL.md","oldText":"## Limitations\n\n- Transcript extraction depends on YouTube's caption availability\n- Auto-generated captions may have errors\n- Some videos have no captions available\n\n### Fallback: yt-dlp\n\nWhen transcript extraction fails:\n\n```bash\nyt-dlp --write-auto-sub --sub-lang en --skip-download \"URL\"\n```","newText":"## Limitations\n\n- Transcript extraction depends on YouTube's caption availability\n- Auto-generated captions may have errors\n- Some videos have no captions available\n- **IP blocking**: YouTube blocks requests from cloud providers (AWS, GCP, Azure, etc.)\n  - Works from personal machines (laptops, desktops)\n  - May fail from VPS/servers\n\n### When Transcript Fails\n\nIf running from a server/VPS:\n\n```bash\n# Use yt-dlp instead (may also be blocked)\nyt-dlp --write-auto-sub --sub-lang en --skip-download \"URL\"\n\n# Or download video and use local Whisper\nyt-dlp -o video.mp4 \"URL\"\nwhisper video.mp4\n```"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":46272,"output":299,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46571,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774795224559,"responseId":"chatcmpl-ba592c4ea0bafcb7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fbcbcb9f","parentId":"8b7905ad","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:41:07.019Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-85f21ab01d741261","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ivo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/youtube-research/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 128 \n 129 - Transcript extraction depends on YouTube's caption availability\n 130 - Auto-generated captions may have errors\n 131 - Some videos have no captions available\n+132 - **IP blocking**: YouTube blocks requests from cloud providers (AWS, GCP, Azure, etc.)\n+133   - Works from personal machines (laptops, desktops)\n+134   - May fail from VPS/servers\n 132 \n-133 ### Fallback: yt-dlp\n+136 ### When Transcript Fails\n 134 \n-135 When transcript extraction fails:\n+138 If running from a server/VPS:\n 136 \n 137 ```bash\n+141 # Use yt-dlp instead (may also be blocked)\n 138 yt-dlp --write-auto-sub --sub-lang en --skip-download \"URL\"\n+143 \n+144 # Or download video and use local Whisper\n+145 yt-dlp -o video.mp4 \"URL\"\n+146 whisper video.mp4\n 139 ```\n 140 \n 141 ## Advanced Usage\n 142 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":132},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774795267016}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8ba8ec4","parentId":"fbcbcb9f","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:41:48.537Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update the error handling in the script to provide better messages:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-9f269a580899e784","name":"edit","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/youtube-research/scripts/youtube_search.py","oldText":"    # Method 1: youtube-transcript-api (most reliable)\n    try:\n        from youtube_transcript_api import YouTubeTranscriptApi\n        \n        api = YouTubeTranscriptApi()\n        transcript_data = api.fetch(video_id, languages=[lang])\n        \n        # Format segments\n        for item in transcript_data:\n            segments.append({\n                \"start\": item.get(\"start\", 0),\n                \"duration\": item.get(\"duration\", 0),\n                \"text\": item.get(\"text\", \"\"),\n            })\n        \n        # Combine text\n        transcript_text = \" \".join([s[\"text\"] for s in segments])\n        method_used = \"youtube-transcript-api\"\n        \n    except ImportError:\n        # Package not installed, fall through to next method\n        pass\n    except Exception as e:\n        # Transcript not available, fall through\n        pass","newText":"    # Method 1: youtube-transcript-api (most reliable)\n    last_error = None\n    try:\n        from youtube_transcript_api import YouTubeTranscriptApi\n        from youtube_transcript_api._errors import IpBlocked, RequestBlocked\n        \n        api = YouTubeTranscriptApi()\n        transcript_data = api.fetch(video_id, languages=[lang])\n        \n        # Format segments\n        for item in transcript_data:\n            segments.append({\n                \"start\": item.get(\"start\", 0),\n                \"duration\": item.get(\"duration\", 0),\n                \"text\": item.get(\"text\", \"\"),\n            })\n        \n        # Combine text\n        transcript_text = \" \".join([s[\"text\"] for s in segments])\n        method_used = \"youtube-transcript-api\"\n        \n    except ImportError:\n        last_error = \"youtube-transcript-api not installed. Run: pip install youtube-transcript-api\"\n        pass\n    except IpBlocked:\n        last_error = \"YouTube is blocking requests from this IP (cloud/VPS detected). Transcripts work from personal machines only.\"\n        pass\n    except RequestBlocked:\n        last_error = \"YouTube blocked the request. This IP may be rate-limited or blocked.\"\n        pass\n    except Exception as e:\n        last_error = f\"Could not fetch transcript: {str(e)}\"\n        pass"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":46614,"output":503,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47117,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774795267021,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b44397d478064d18"}}
