{"type":"message","id":"5a97fd07","parentId":"d7f726ca","timestamp":"2026-03-29T15:13:18.045Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-9faae6557fa56d7d","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This thing is definitely not safe.  Think of the literal worst thing somebody could do if they logged into your computer.  So maybe that's like they texted your ex and asked them to get back together.  Or maybe they'd drain all your bank accounts by installing Claude bot.  You have now opened the possibility for an AI agent to do that to you tomorrow morning.  And you might be thinking, oh, it probably won't do that.  Yeah, probably not.  But it's probably not a good enough assurance for you.  I think the only completely way to set this up right now is first set this up on a different computer.  I know you do not need to be buying Macminis like everybody on Twitter was doing.  The cheapest way to go about this if you don't already have a machine at home is to use some kind of Claude hosting.  But don't just host this on a separate computer.  Also create separate accounts.  If you have Claude bot on a second computer but you're logged into your Gmail or some other account,  this is arguably just as bad and just as much have it can be wrecked.  And even then when you do have separate accounts, separate computer,  there's still a risk that your Claude bot is doing something you don't want it to do.  Even if it has its own email address, it still has the power to email your boss and say you want to resign.  And sure, your boss might notice that's coming from a different email address and not actually let you go.  But then you still have to explain what it is you prompted your AI that led it to try to quit your job.  So there isn't really a fully safe way to do this.  And lastly, make sure you either running a model locally or you're setting strict limits on token usage because this stuff can get very expensive.  So with that giant warning, use it 